                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <persName
                            type="to">Inman, Akers and Inman</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>If linters are intended for and adaptable for manufacture of ammunition, would
                    probably be held contraband. Insurance issued by War Risk Bureau does not cover
                    contraband articles.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
